Just watching someone else execute a lift doesn't tell you much about how you can perform a lift.

It might show you how a movement may (or may not!) look like. 

A "how to do x" tutorial ideally will be specific to every individual. And can only really be created by 2 individuals.

Either the person himself having spent a long time (probably years) understanding his/her body mechanics 

Or the individual's coach or physiotherapist who understands (a) Proper movement mechanics of the movement and (b)  
